low on mana after just re-doing Aego.  So, I say to my SK tank Keep aggro, I'm gonna try something. Mwahahaha<br><br>I stand back, load up Tears of Prexus, Tears of Solusek and Tears of Druzzil and wait for the next pull and my Shaman friend to Malo.  As soon as he did, and the chanter tashed, Tears of Prexus, Jboots, Tears of Solusek, Jboots Tears of Druzzil.<br><br>Oh my dear god...  the mob dropped so fast...<br>With a Naki's Studded ring I was able to Finish casting the next rain before the third wave hit, and amazingly enough I didn't get a single resist or Crit.  I sent the mob directly into run mode in under 20 seconds.<br><br>690, 690, 645, 690, 645, 600, 645, 600, 600 in just under 20 seconds. It used near half my mana (my gear is sub par) and my whole group including myself was in awe.<br><br>5805 damage in under twenty seconds I was doing ~300dps<br><br>I had to wait about half a second before Tears of Prexus to repop, so I coulda kept it going until I ran oom or got summoned.<br><br>I know finding mobs that aren't resistant to any elements is rare, but jeez... you have to see this yourselves to believe it...<br><br>I wish I got a screenshot of my SK friend saying: &quot;omg look at its health drop&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyaleldar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaleldar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/02 11:01:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18009.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ultimate Wizard DPS... (provided no resists)</span><hr size=1> Very nice Xar , very very nice<br>just wants me to get up there in levels when i see things like this.<br>Did you take any damage at all ? Just wondering if you also drew